#: preinst.in:93
msgid "ATTENTION - POSTGRESQL PACKAGE TRANSITION"
msgstr ""

#: preinst.in:95
#, sh-format
msgid ""
"The \\`postgresql' package no longer holds the PostgreSQL server itself,\n"
"and now  automatically  depend  on  the  latest  major release, so the\n"
"previously installed  PostgreSQL  release  can still serve connections,\n"
"and migration to the new major release can be easily done.\n"
"\n"
"We now ship officially supported PostgreSQL releases under the names\n"
"like \\`postgresql-VERSION', for example \\`postgresql-$PGMAJOR'.\n"
"\n"
"Executable names now have version on them, for example \\`psql-$PGMAJOR',\n"
"\\`pg_dump-$PGMAJOR', \\`pg_ctl-$PGMAJOR' and so on. Systemd service names "
"also\n"
"have version on them, for example, to start PostgreSQL $PGMAJOR:\n"
"\n"
"  sudo systemctl start postgresqld-$PGMAJOR.service\n"
"\n"
"The executables without version on them point to their corresponding\n"
"executables of the currently latest release, for example, \\`psql' points\n"
"to \\`psql-$PGMAJOR'. There are no versioned systemd service name.\n"
"\n"
"If you are using the PostgreSQL from AOSC OS to serve data, please note\n"
"that the currently installed PostgreSQL $OLDMAJOR must be stopped and "
"removed\n"
"in order to continue the transition (your data will not be removed).\n"
"After the transition, you must install the old release in order to\n"
"either continue using without migration, or migrate to PostgreSQL $PGMAJOR:\n"
"\n"
"  sudo oma install postgresql-$OLDMAJOR\n"
"\n"
"To continue using PostgreSQL $OLDMAJOR, run the following command:\n"
"\n"
"  sudo systemctl start postgresqld-$OLDMAJOR.service\n"
"\n"
"Or, after performing the migration, you can remove the old release and\n"
"use the new server:\n"
"\n"
"  systemctl start postgresql-$PGMAJOR\n"
"  sudo oma remove postgresql-$OLDMAJOR\n"
msgstr ""

#: preinst.in:133
msgid ""
"The old PostgreSQL server which is installed before this transition\n"
"is still running.\n"
"\n"
"Due to the package scheme transition, it is required to shut down the\n"
"running old server in order to prevent damage of the data and to aid\n"
"the migration to the later release.\n"
"\n"
"Please shut down any services that uses the PostgreSQL on your system\n"
"now, and press Enter to shut down the PostgreSQL server."
msgstr ""

#: preinst.in:146
#, sh-format
msgid ""
"The new major release of PostgreSQL ($PGMAJOR) is installed on your\n"
"system. PostgreSQL $OLDMAJOR will be kept installed on your system until\n"
"the next major release. You can run \\`oma hold postgresql-$OLDMAJOR' to\n"
"prevent it from being automatically removed.\n"
msgstr ""

#: preinst.in:153
#, sh-format
msgid ""
"To migrate from a previous PostgreSQL release, you can use either\n"
"\\`pg_upgrade' or \\`pg_dump'. Refer the following link to learn more\n"
"about migration:\n"
"\n"
"  $DOCURL\n"
msgstr ""

#: preinst.in:161
msgid ""
"Due to the transition, this upgrade must be manually performed.\n"
"Rejecting upgrade."
msgstr ""

#: preinst.in:164 preinst.in:259 preinst.in:270
msgid "The upgrade is interrupted."
msgstr ""

#: preinst.in:166
msgid "Please run 'oma fix-broken -n' to try again."
msgstr ""
